<p>The <code>output</code> tag sets the output type for PAD processing.</p>

<h2>Output Types</h2>
<p>PAD supports several output types:</p>
<ul>
  <li><strong>web</strong> - Default, outputs to browser</li>
  <li><strong>console</strong> - Output for command line</li>
  <li><strong>file</strong> - Write output to file</li>
  <li><strong>download</strong> - Trigger file download</li>
</ul>

<h2>Syntax</h2>
<pre>{open}output 'web'{close}
{open}output 'console'{close}
{open}output 'file'{close}
{open}output 'download'{close}</pre>

<h2>Current Output Mode</h2>
<p>This page is using the default <strong>web</strong> output mode.</p>

<h2>Example: Download Mode</h2>
<p>To create a downloadable file:</p>
<pre>{open}output 'download'{close}
{open}file name='report', ext='txt'{close}
  Report content here...
{open}/file{close}</pre>

<h2>Example: File Output</h2>
<p>To write output to a file instead of displaying:</p>
<pre>{open}output 'file'{close}
{open}file dir='path/to/', name='output', ext='html'{close}
  &lt;html&gt;...&lt;/html&gt;
{open}/file{close}</pre>

<h2>Note</h2>
<p>The output tag affects how PAD delivers its final output. Changing it mid-page can have unexpected results. It's typically set at the beginning of processing.</p>
